public interface CleanableObject
An object that can be cleaned; i.e., for destroyed fields which should be released
Author:
Andrew

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void clean()
    Instructs this object to search its members for any object which has been destroyed, and release the pointer to it.
